Cure

by: Arshia Nayebnazar

This game was made for my level 2 project at The League of Amazing Programmers.
Click here to download and play!

1. Why I Made This Game

I greatly enjoy playing intense and fast-paced games. When creating this game, I thought of forming a type of game that would fit these enjoyable traits. Eventually, a fun zombie game came to my mind!

2. What I Learned

There were some levels that may have been too difficult to go through. Additionally, there were some unfair aspects to the game, in which the zombie could spawn and touch the player right as the user reaches the end of the level. Overall, I gained recommendations on improving efficiency and enjoyment of the game.

3. Architecture of My Game

Many different parts of my game contribute and interact with my game greatly, including the main class, a game panel, an object manager class, and a game object class, in which it assists with the creation of my objects and their characteristics. Each class interacts with each other by using variables and other components to communicate and attach the game together as one.

4. Technical Implementation

I believe my game included several different objects and components that elevated the game's fun, including bushes and the player's ability to hide in them. I am mostly proud of the "zombie" class as well as the code within the object manager that relates to the zombie. To elaborate, I enjoyed creating the zombie and its traits in the game, including the steps in which I had to make the zombie follow the player as well as adjusting its speed and spawn time for increased enjoyment.

5. Most Challenging Part

Some challenges included unknown causes for an object's inability to do actions correctly. To overcome these challenges, I primarily attempted to organize and figure out which blocks of code should be moved around to produce the desired results.

6. Future Fixes and Updates

In addition to creating more levels, I would greatly enjoy expanding the map, creating new environments as well. Furthermore, I think an addition of new objects to help make the game more enjoyable would be a good idea as well. Fixing bugs and efficiency for the game would be significant.
